on-chalant =( afterwards..most likely a lowbe wanting to see the stats i am thinking....So he asks me, he says Do you have the drop from Fear? I do a Shift Up and repeat the above mentioned reply. <br>
<br>
This is where my casual Everquest rutine and luck took the biggest cosmic u-turn since I started playing. The man, Marck, is actually a level 65 cleric from Evil Raiders no less. Him and his 60+ buddies were &quot;Just wondering&quot; if i could round up about 6 melee types and a healer because they just so happen to be standing in front of the most highly contested wizard mob with the bulk of Fear cleared out..waiting...for some lucky wizard to find his way down there with his friends and loot a very gift wrapped Green Oil.<br>
<br>
Thankfully, in my career of Everquest, such little qurks have long since sent me into a unrecognizable babble of /tells and /gu's..and has finely tuned me  into a being who can shoot off about 20 tells to 100 different people in the blink of an eye. To put it bluntly &quot;I was *ON* it&quot; My status immediatly went from &quot;Shall I quad wyverns...or giants tonight?&quot; to &quot;Type Faster&quot; <br>
<br>
Who did I call on? About the only people I could call on, My rebukers, my allies, my friends...The people at Random Acts and Gathering of Banners. I did my best not to cause an uproar and to handle things calmly. As a result i was able to bring together a collection of my close friends, thier friends, and their friends friends. Together, the Enraged Golem went down flawlessly without so much as an add.<br>
<br>
I haven't exactly always given credit when credit is due, but I wont let this go unsaid. This, and other achievements before, have only been possible for me thru your kindness and understanding. I have achieved many many great things...things that I had planned to achieve..and some things that I haddn't! You've made my achievements worth-while, filled with good memories and fun. I couldn't ask for a better set of friends. <br>
<br>
I'll give a shout out to those names which i can recall.I wanna thank Tinnax, first off, cuz he bit the dust when he went the other way in Fear...which isn't usually something that exictes you when you charge head-long into fear with only your friends word to go on that it will be clear. Thanks for your help!<br>
<br>
I'd like to thank Toggler, Ortaak, Patofnaud, Tigon,  some paladin guy one of the GoBers invited *cant remember his name*, and Kritox. If i missed anyone, your name is typed in invisable ink right here (       )  =D<br>
<br>
